  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Level Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Implementing strict identification verification processes\n\n4. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory compliance departments\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial systems.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering prevention?",
